25/05/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The opposition Great Union Party (BBP) elected Yalcin Topcu as its new leader Sunday (May 24th), succeeding Muhsin Yazicioglu, died in a March helicopter crash. Topcu was the only candidate running for the post in the third round of voting. Yazicioglu and five others were killed when his helicopter crashed in a mountainous area in the southern province of Kahramanmaras, as they returned from a campaign rally. (Yeni Safak, Vatan, Anadolu news agency - 25/05/09) 
